Reasoning: The paper discusses the semantics of natural language determiner phrases and proposes a new treatment using a richly typed system. This topic falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and natural language processing (NLP). The paper also discusses the use of logic and lambda calculus, which are relevant to the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a many-sorted logic for semantical representations is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and the development of formal semantics. Finally, the paper discusses the Montagovian generative lexicon, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and the development of computational models for natural language understanding.
